analysis.summary: President Trump signed a revised free trade agreement with South Korea, marking his administration's first bilateral trade deal. While touted as a significant achievement, analysts note the agreement contains few fundamental changes from the previous Obama-era pact and lacks promised currency manipulation provisions that were previously announced.
